{"id":79621,"date":"2022-07-03T15:29:16","date_gmt":"2022-07-03T13:29:16","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=79621"},"modified":"2022-08-12T09:49:15","modified_gmt":"2022-08-12T07:49:15","slug":"costa-rica-3-week-itinerary","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/costa-rica-3-week-itinerary\/","title":{"rendered":"Costa Rica 3-Week Itinerary: The Complete Travel Guide"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-ultimate-costa-rica-3-week-itinerary\">Ultimate Costa Rica 3-Week Itinerary<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Costa Rica is known worldwide for its incredible conservation and protection of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/tips\/wildlife-tourism\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">wildlife<\/a>. The locals have great respect for the animals and sea life, and seeing exotic creatures close to the towns and villages is a completely normal part of daily life. The government policies reflect this, with strict rules that prohibit building on\/near the beaches and laws that work to protect endangered species and natural habitats.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26033944\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-5-648x810.jpg\" alt=\"Costa Rica 3 week itinerary horse riding\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Costa Rica 3 week itinerary horse riding\" class=\"wp-image-74653 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 648px) 100vw, 648px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26033944\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-5-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26033944\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-5-480x60