a-18.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p><strong>By Bus or Shuttle:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The public buses (MEPE) leave from San Jose to Puerto Viejo about five times a day and take roughly 4.5 hours. <a href=\"https:\/\/12go.asia\/en\/travel\/barcelona\/madrid?people=2&amp;date=2022-04-20&amp;direction=forward\">It&#x2019;s the cheapest way to travel<\/a>, with tickets starting from around 10 USD. If you want to be picked up from your hotel, and have a slightly more comfortable journey, opt for a shared shuttle with other travelers. The price starts from around 50 USD and takes approximately 5 hours; it&#x2019;s a bit longer because of hotel pickups.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--transport \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--transport\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/transport-san-jose-puerto-viejo\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Book a bus or shuttle to Puerto Viejo<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/22102638\/nauyaca-waterfall-costa-rica-2.jpg\" alt=\"Costa Rica 3 week itinerary nauyaca waterfalls\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Costa Rica 3 week itinerary nauyaca waterfalls\" class=\"wp-image-78754 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/22102638\/nauyaca-waterfall-costa-rica-2.