v class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p><strong>By Bus or Shuttle:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The public bus + ferry is definitely the cheapest way to travel to Santa Teresa, but it does take quite a long time (5-7 hours). When you get off the ferry at Paquera, take the bus to Cobano and change bus to Mal Pais (a town 15 minutes from Santa Teresa).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Shuttles are available throughout the day but pre-booking them is recommended. Costs for a trip, including the ferry, should be between 60 &#x2013; 85 USD.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--transport \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--transport\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.12go.asia\/en\/travel\/monteverde-puntarenas\/santa-teresa-beach\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Book a shuttle to Santa Teresa from Monteverde<\/a><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26224610\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-12.jpg\" alt=\"beaches costa rica\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"beaches costa rica\" class=\"wp-image-74767 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26224610\/santa-teresa-costa-rica-12.jpg 1281w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/26224610\/santa-teres